'''Elizabeth "Betty" Beecroft''' née '''Skirrow''' (1748–1812) was farmer's wife who bought the [[Kirkstall forge]] in 1779 and then managed it, making and selling [[iron]] and [[ironware]]. Later, she focussed upon the farm's produce such as selling butter.<ref name=DNB/>

